events.name: GDG Cloud Dublin - April 2018
events.description:
GDG Cloud Dublin - April 2018 is our monthly meetup that offers speaker sessions across Cloud, applications, microservices, and more!

This month the talk is going to be on Chaos Engineering on Kubernetes in GCP lead by Javier Arrieta.

Javier has more than 35 years of programming experience with more than 25 years of OOP programming. He has been giving several talks on microservices, system architecture/ops, functional scala, etc. in various meetups and internal talks.

We are looking forward to meeting you at Google - Gordon House on April 19, 2018.

NOTE: Please register for your free ticket on Eventbrite! We have limited seats so hurry up!

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/gdg-cloud-dublin-april-2018-tickets-44953471042?ref=eios&aff=eios

GDG Cloud Dublin Team

events.name: Serverless with GDG Cloud Dublin
events.description:
Hello GDG Cloud Dublin members,

We are really happy to announce our first event of the year. Save the date April 4th and join us for learning more about Serverless along other topics and mingle with the community at Google HQ Dublin

We have organised for you really interesting sessions with our very own GDE and Software Engineers from Workday and NearForm who will be talking about Serverless.

Agenda:

6.30 - 6.45 pm - Welcome & Registration
6.45 - 7.00 pm - Networking / Food & Refreshments
7.00 - 7.25 pm - Serverless and containers: The best of both worlds by Ignacio León
7.30 - 8.00 pm - To serverless or to not serverless that is the question by David Gonzalez - GDE for GCP
8.00 - 8.25 pm Serverless SPAs at Workday by Ana Vallejo & Kevin Gaffney

NOTE: Please notice that meetup is locked for RSVP, if you want to attend please register on this link: http://bit.ly/2TTHahZ

About our Speakers

Ignacio León - Cloud Customer Engineer @ Google
He help companies develop creative cloud solutions and architectures to solve their business challenges

Ana Vallejo - Senior Software Engineer @ Workday

She used to be full stack engineer. Spanish blood, Irish heart. Ana enjoys travelling, food, books, beer and nature.

David Gonzalez - Devops Consultant @ Nearform

GDE, author of several books and devops enthusiast. David is always looking for new challenges, lately around containers and cloud.

Kevin Gaffney - Principal Engineer UI @ Workday

He is the first front end engineer in Workday Dublin seven years ago. Kevin is a Coffee geek, book worm and enjoy travelling at speed.

Food and Refreshments will be provided.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam #1 & Cloud Next Extended
events.description:
Hello GDG Cloud Dublin members,

As we promised in twitter and last meetup announcements, we were preparing really cool stuff for all of you. We would like to invite you this time to our GDG Cloud Study Jams sessions.

NOTES:
- RSVP here: http://bit.ly/2HZbdi4
- Sessions are limited to 40 attendees each track

Are you wondering what Study Jams are?

Study Jams are community-run study groups for developers. This is a great opportunity to bring members of the community together to learn something in person.

What will you learn ?
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin?
Then Join us for the Cloud Study Jam

Get official Google training, valued at $55+, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes and Machine Learning.
After the sessions you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home.

Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and an additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want

What do we need from you ?
- To bring your computer and charger with a Browser ( Chrome or Firefox )
- Enthusiasm & Commitment, as the sessions will run for 4 weeks approximately
- Be ready to learn and have fun

What topics will be covered?
There will be 2 tracks:

- Kubernetes
- Data, ML and AI

Where?
- Google HQ

When?
- It will be run every Thursday from April 11th until May 9nd

Time?
6.30 pm to 8.30 pm

FAQs

Do I need to register for each session?

Yes, sessions are independent and a new set of tickets will be released each week

Could I join even if I didn't attend the first session?

Yes, you are always welcome to join, in the middle, on the last session.

What if I finish all sessions at home after the first?

Awesome, you are a rock star, you could still join us and keep going on the advanced track

Snacks & Refreshments will be provided

Follow us in twitter: https://twitter.com/gdgclouddublin

upcoming.name: Cloud Workshop - Machine Learning
upcoming.description:
Hello everyone,

We are super excited to invite you to join us for a free full workshop night about Machine Learning on Google Cloud facilitated by Abdallah Abedraba from Google.

This workshop will cover from beginners to in-depth content on Machine Learning on Google Cloud.

Starting from an introductory level, we will be advancing in difficulty with the succeeding sessions. If by the end of the night you haven't finished, don't worry you can take your work and continue working, we have your back and will provide support.

IMPORTANT: RSVP only over eventbrite: https://gdgclouddublin-july-ml-workshop.eventbrite.com

Agenda
This is a 4 hour training starting from 5 pm to 9 pm:
5:00 pm: Registration and refreshments
5:15 pm: A tour of Qwiklabs and GCP and getting started with Cloud Shell & gcloud
6:15 pm: Cloud Natural Language API: Qwik Start + Video Intelligence: Qwik Start
7:15 pm: Break
7:30 pm: Classify Images of Cloud Using Cloud ML API
8:15 pm: Implementing an AI Chatbot with Dialogflow
9:00 pm: Workshop close

Requirements:

Bring your computer :) Don't have one? Don't worry you can pair with someone.

Get to know our facilitator,

Abdallah Abedraba, is part of the Developer Relations team at Google helping to drive developers success and awareness of the Open Standards & Google Technologies by working closely with Developer Communities.

A third Palestinian, a third Kenyan and a third Spanish, he loves strongly typed programming languages, Free & Open Source Software, maths, chess, hiking and a good morning run! You can find him on Twitter at @aabedraba

Follow us in twitter: https://twitter.com/gdgclouddublin

FAQs:

I don't know anything about Machine Learning and/or Cloud, can I still go?

Yes, You will come in with little or no prior cloud knowledge, and come out with practical experience that you can apply to your first GCP project

upcoming.name: Cloud Run Club - Dublin
upcoming.description:
Hello everyone,

Thinking already about plans for Summer?

Save the date August 6th, and Join us for a special event that is being run across many cities of the World and you will be able to be part of it.

IMPORTANT: RSVP on Eventbrite: https://gdgclouddublin-aug-cloud-run-club.eventbrite.com

What is Cloud Run Club?

Cloud Run Club is an event for developers to learn about Cloud Run, serverless and container technologies. Attendees will meet Googlers and other community members while getting hands on with Cloud Run.

What is Cloud Run?

Cloud Run is a managed compute platform that enables you to run stateless containers that are invocable via HTTP requests. Cloud Run is serverless: it abstracts away all infrastructure management, so you can focus on what matters most — building great applications.

The event will include:

- Tech talks / Hands-on labs
- Optional 5k fun-run
- Food and drinks

Agenda:

5.00 pm - 6.00 pm Register and Mingle
6.00pm - 7.00 pm Cloud Run Workshop by Guillaume Laforge - Developer Advocate at Google
7.00pm - 7.45 pm Optional Fun Run
8.00pm - 9.00 pm Food, Drinks, and Conversation

Requirements:
- Bring your computer, don't have one? Don't worry you can always pair with someone
- If you are planning to participate over the run, bring your gear for running, comfortable shoes and clothes.

FAQ’s
Can I go to the tech talks and skip the run?
Sure, Run is optional.

What is the 5k fun-run?
Bond with other developers while enjoying a scenic run. You are also more than welcome to stay at Google to continue working on the Qwiklabs course

Follow us in twitter: https://twitter.com/gdgclouddublin
